CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 24, 1961, pg. A32, reads: "Little League Braves - In third place by reason of three wins in eight games, above are the members of the Little League Braves. From left to right, kneeling: William Abramonitz, Ronald Wright, Reginald Bennett, Roderick Horne, James Montgomery, Curtiss McGee and Carl Morris.  Standing: Rickey Moloney, Donald Alexander, Charles Butler, Tyland Richardson, Craig Clark, Montell Brundage, Amos Lawson, Fred Hill and George Morris.  Standing behind the youngsters are: Coach Elbert Montgomery and Manager Joseph Geller. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Braves Little League baseball team, from left, kneeling: William Abramonitz, Ronald Wright, Reginald Bennett, Roderick Horne, James Montgomery, Curtiss McGee, and Carl Morris; second row: Rickey Moloney, Donald Alexander, Charles Butler, Tyland Richardson, Craig Clark, Montell Brundage, Amos Lawson, Fred Hill, and George Morris; rear: coach Elbert Montgomery, and manager Joseph Geller, posed possibly on Ammon Field, another version
